This paper is about knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning embeddings for entities and relations in a knowledge graph, which is a type of database (cs.DB). The paper also mentions experiments on benchmark datasets, which suggests a focus on evaluation and performance (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity linking and relation extraction, which fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
